<br>
General Information<br>
The league will run from March 17th, 2003 until April 26th, a total of six weeks. The sign-up sheet will be available at Gallop’s from March 1st till March 15th. The schedule for the mandatory weekly games will be posted at Gallop’s on March 17th on the bulletin board on the gaming side, and also on the Heavy Hand message board at heavyhand.org. There will also be a 750 point tournament at Gallop’s on May 3. What follows are the guidelines for the league. <br>
<br>
Army Lists<br>
All army lists published in a 3rd edition codex (including Daemonhunters) and all lists and special rules published in White Dwarf, Chapter Approved, or Index Astartes are allowed except for the following: Imperial Armoured Company and full Death Company armies. Note that this does include all of the rules still deemed experimental or trial, i.e. Cursed Foundings. All armies must use the most recent versions of their codex and/or special rules. Also allowed are the minor psychic powers, vehicles from the Imperial Armour books, and the Grey Death Legion rules (This is Jim’s Army List and a copy of it will be available for all to read). For the first 3 weeks of the league, all armies will use 500 points and then 750 points for the last three weeks. For the 3 weeks using 500 points, we will be using a slightly modified version of the force organization chart. All armies may choose between 1 to 6 troop units and 0-1 of all other unit types. Note: this mainly means that you are not required to have an HQ choice and are limited to one of any choice aside from troops. Another modification is that forces required to take a certain troop or HQ choice may opt not to take these while the league remains at 500 points (i.e. Space Wolf HQ and Grey Hunters, Imperial Guard Command Platoon, Ork Warboss, etc. will not be required in 500 point armies). We will also be using the new assault rules found in White Dwarf #272. Armies are not required to be painted by the beginning of the league, but it will be required for the Tournament on May 3rd. <br>
<br>
Weekly Play<br>
All players will have one mandatory scheduled game for each of the six weeks. Players will also be able to play one in-league pickup game each. Pick-up game results will still be factored in to league results. Pick-up games, however, may not be played against the same person you are scheduled to play that week. Certain scenarios will be required for your mandatory games. All weekly scenarios will be posted beside the schedule at Gallop’s the Saturday before the week of its use (so the week 1 scenario will be posted on March 15th). Results slips will be available at Gallop’s and must be submitted after every game<br>
<br>
